{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011hWagSCWKM3xzAZh1D33d9","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me provide you with a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've successfully read the key files from your Lord of the RNGs feature. Here's what exists:\n\n### **1. LordOfRngsContext.tsx** (312 lines)\nComplete file provided above. This is the main context provider that manages:\n- **State**: activeRound, tierStatuses, userHistory, selectedTier, entryCount\n- **Loading states**: loading, joining, buyingMore, claiming\n- **Actions**: setSelectedTier, setEntryCount, joinTierRound, buyMoreEntriesAction, claimPayout, leaveRound, refreshRounds\n- **Effects**:\n  - Auto-initializes mock rounds on mount\n  - Polls for round updates every 2 seconds\n  - Subscribes to active round updates with auto-claim for winners\n  - Auto-transitions back to lobby after round completion (3s for winners, 1.5s for losers)\n  - Checks for existing active rounds when wallet connects\n  - Auto-selects tier based on active round\n\n### **2. mock-simulation.ts** (492 lines) \n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/utils/mock-simulation.ts` (NOT in context folder)\n\nComplete file provided above. Key features:\n- **Constants**: 60s countdown, 5s spin, 3s reveal, min 2 players\n- **Round lifecycle**: waiting → countdown → spinning → revealing → complete\n- **Mock store**: tracks rounds, tier rounds, listeners, mock player timers\n- **Player actions**: joinRound, buyMoreEntries, subscribeToRound\n- **Phase transitions**: startCountdown, startSpinning, resolveRound, completeRound\n- **Mock player simulation**: auto-adds 1-3 players initially, 2-5 during countdown\n- **Fairness data**: generates seedHash, serverSeed, blockHash, vrfProof\n- **Event emissions**: emits to boss-raid and player-profile event buses\n\n### **3. types.ts** (77 lines)\nProvided above. Defines:\n- `RoundPhase`: \"waiting\" | \"countdown\" | \"spinning\" | \"revealing\" | \"complete\"\n- `PlayerEntry`: address, entries, displayName?, color\n- `Round`: complete round structure with all phases, fairness data, results\n- `TierStatus`: tier, entryAmount, currentRound\n- `JoinRoundParams`, `BuyMoreEntriesParams`\n- `PLAYER_COLORS`: 12-color palette (neon green for current user, various colors for others)\n\n### **Directory Structure**\n```\nlord-of-rngs/\n├── components/\n│   ├── ActiveRoundView.tsx\n│   ├── CountdownTimer.tsx\n│   ├── index.ts\n│   ├── TierLobby.tsx\n│   ├── TierRoundView.tsx\n│   └── WheelVisualization.tsx\n├── context/\n│   └── LordOfRngsContext.tsx\n├── index.ts\n├── types.ts\n└── utils/\n    ├── chain.ts\n    ├── mock-simulation.ts\n    └── odds.ts\n```\n\n### **Key Exports** (from index.ts)\n- `LordOfRngsProvider`, `useLordOfRngs`\n- Components: `WheelVisualization`, `TierLobby`, `TierRoundView`, `ActiveRoundView`, `CountdownTimer`\n- Types: `Round`, `PlayerEntry`, `RoundPhase`, `TierStatus`, `PLAYER_COLORS`\n- Utils: `truncateAddress`, `calculateOdds`, `calculateSingleOdds`, `formatOdds`\n\n**Note**: The mock-simulation.ts file is in `utils/`, not in `context/` as you initially asked about. The `context/mock-simulation.ts` file does not exist."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af26e89 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 40427\ntool_uses: 9\nduration_ms: 19273</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc54e4bc-17c9-4774-b61a-be37e6291ab9","uuid":"03e3a4ee-ace7-4687-bd54-921bcab12ac0","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the full contents of these files and report back their complete content:\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/context/LordOfRngsContext.tsx`\n2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/context/mock-simulation.ts` (if it exists)\n\nAlso check what files exist in the l